#Text=West Chester ( Pennsylvania )
#Text=West Chester is a borough in Chester County in the Philadelphia Region of Pennsylvania .
#Text=It is the county seat .
#Text=By bus
#Text=SEPTA Route 104 , follows West Chester Pike into Downtown West Chester , ending in a stop on the campus of West Chester University .
#Text=By air
#Text=Brandywine Airport , 1205 Ward Ave. , ☏ +1610 692-6100 , fax : +1610 692-6213 , ✉ airportmanager@n99.com .
#Text=Small , private airport for corporate or personal flights .
#Text=Philadelphia International Airport .
#Text=About 45 minutes away from West Chester , the Philadelphia International Airport is much bigger than the Brandywine Airport .
#Text=It has many commercial airlines that fly in from all over the world .
#Text=Get around
#Text=No taxi services run steadily through downtown West Chester , but the downtown area is an easy walk from one end to another .
#Text=Walking around downtown is nice because of the historic atmosphere and brick sidewalks with a mixture of shops , bars , restaurants , and local offices .
#Text=See
#Text=The entire town is rich with history .
#Text=The cobblestone streets were put in the 1700s .
#Text=The soldiers of the Revolutionary War walked through West Chester on those very cobblestones .
#Text=Visitors along with residents marvel at the building where Abraham Lincoln started his journey towards the presidency .
#Text=West Chester has more than 3,000 structures built before the colonial time which puts the entire downtown on the list of National Registered Historic Places .

#Text=The town was home for the legendary African-American folk artist , Horace Pippin , Pulitzer Prize winning composer Samuel O. Barber ( 1910-1981 ) along with many other aspiring and proven artists .
#Text=Chester County Historical Society ( Museum & Library ) , 225 N. High Street , ☏ +1610 692-4800 .
#Text=The Museum & Library are open Tue - Sat , 10 am to 5 pm , The Museum Shop is open Monday - Saturday , 10 am to 5 pm .
#Text=Definitely bigger and fancier than your average Historical Society Museum .
#Text=One of the buildings was originally an opera house designed by the same architect who designed the capital dome in Washington , DC .
#Text=Not as good as a Smithsonian or something , but if you 're into history at all and you 're in the area , it 's definitely worth seeing .
#Text=Genealogical and newspaper records at the library are very comprehensive .
#Text=The Court House , 2 N High street .
#Text=is a sight to see .
#Text=It is one of the most historic buildings in the town .
#Text=William Penn established Chester County as a member of the three first counties of the Colonial Pennsylvania in 1682 .
#Text=In 1724 a courthouse was built near the Delaware River in Chester .
#Text=Because of population growth the courthouse moved inland into West Chester .
#Text=A court house was constructed between 1784 and 1786 on High street in the middle of West Chester .
#Text=This establishment is listed on the National Register of Historic Places .
#Text=Do
#Text=There are so many exciting things to do in West Chester .
#Text=With all of the restaurants , bars and shopping there is an activity for everyone .
#Text=West Chester University is a major attraction to the area .
#Text=Many families visit the campus in hopes of sending their children to a highly accredited university .
#Text=Because the school is located in the heart of the town it is mainly seen as a college town , which means the nightlife is always active and exciting .
#Text=For those who enjoy golf there are more than five golf courses in West Chester .
#Text=Parking is free all weekend in the Parking Garages & Lots and on-street meters .
#Text=And you never have to feed the meters after 5 pm everyday .
#Text=Televised home shopping channel QVC 's headquarters and main broadcast studios are just north of town .
#Text=Studio tours , which are $ 7.50 ( $ 6 for children ) , run several times daily , and tickets to special live-audience events are available in advance via the website .
#Text=A company store selling fan ware with the QVC logo as well as a small selection of popular items is on the premises .
#Text=For those interested in the arts , downtown West Chester is home to more than 15 shops containing art gallery work .
#Text=American Helicopter Museum , 1220 American Boulevard , ☏ +1 610-436-9600 .
#Text=Wed - Sat 10am-5pm ; Sun 12n-5pm ; Mon - Tue ( prescheduled groups only ) .
#Text=The American Helicopter Museum and Education Center is an aviation museum devoted exclusively to helicopters .
#Text=They collect , restore and display historic aircraft and chronicle the origin and development of rotary wing aircraft .
#Text=This museum can be interesting to actual pilots down to people who know nothing about helicopters .
#Text=Adults $ 6 ; Seniors $ 5 ; Students ( with ID ) & Children ( 2-12 ) $ 4 , ( under 2 ) free with paying adult .
#Text=Northbrook Canoe Company , 1810 Beagle Road , toll-free : +1-800-898-2279 .
#Text=may-sept 9am-4pm .
#Text=Offers canoeing , kayaking , tubing and splash boat trips .
#Text=West Chester Railroad Heritage Association , 250 E. Market St. , ☏ +1610 430-2233 .
#Text=Call for rentals and charters .

#Text=The purpose of the West Chester Railroad Heritage Association is to collect , preserve , and exhibit railroad equipment and artifacts relating to railroading with emphasis on the southeastern Pennsylvania region ; to operate a demonstration railroad for the education and enjoyment of the public .
#Text=West Chester Growers Market , Church St & Chestnut St. May-Dec : Sa 9AM-1PM .
#Text=The first producer-only market in southeastern Pennsylvania , in their 17th year .
#Text=Wide variety of locally grown produce in season along with baked goods , cheese , meat and other farm-market staples .
#Text=Buy
#Text=West
#Text=Chester is known for its quaint boutiques and trendy shops .
#Text=Gay street is a central area for shopping .
#Text=Malena 's Vintage boutique , Plane Janea and Niche are just some of the fashionable shops located on Gay Street .
#Text=The unique finds in Malena 's Boutique range from 50s cocktail dresses to Gucci bags .
#Text=This little store has everything a fashionista would want .
#Text=Plain Jane sells any type of beauty product a girl could need .
#Text=This affordable store has jeans and nice button-downs for men along with beautifully , colorful dresses for women .
#Text=These are just a few of the shopping experiences West Chester has to offer .
#Text=One place that is frequented by the local kids during the summertime is the Brandywine River .
#Text=There are plenty of rope swings and little spots to hang out .
#Text=The rope swings are n't really a tourist spot , they are more like a hangout spot for residents of West Chester .
#Text=The Brandywine River Park is also a popular place for companies and large groups to spend the day .
#Text=There are also canoe and kayak tours during the spring and summer seasons .
#Text=Malena 's Boutique , 145 West Gay Street , ☏ +1610 738-9952 .
#Text=M-Sat:12-7 ; Sun:12-4.
#Text=The unique finds in Malena 's Boutique range from 50s cocktail dresses to Gucci bags
#Text=Fairman 's Skate Shop , 43 West Gay Street , ☏ +1 610-344-9959 .
#Text=Established in 1977 , FAIRMAN’S is one of the East Coast 's oldest Skate , Snow and Surf shops .
